  text: Here's how you can create a lookup formula in Excel that returns results based on header names and works when dragged down (as requested).

## The Principle

If you want to fill cells I2:I5 with results that depend on the header name in column H (where H2:H5 contain "Name", "Category", etc.), and the data is in columns A to E, you would use an INDEX-MATCH formula in Excel. The Python script will show in those cells what formula to use, as a hint for users.

## What Formula to Use

In Excel 2019,…(truncated)

